{
  "page": "Cannibal Bay",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Cannibal Bay</b> is a legendary place said by sailors to lie somewhere in the <a href=\"/index.php/Shivering_Sea\" title=\"Shivering Sea\">Shivering Sea</a>. It is said that ships enter Cannibal Bay only to find themselves trapped forever as the sea freezes behind them. Legend also claims some of the thousand ships entombed there are inhabited by the descendants of the original crews, who survive by feasting on the flesh of the newly trapped sailors.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafbeyond_the_free_cities:_the_shivering_sea.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafbeyond_the_free_cities:_the_shivering_sea.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Margate\" title=\"Margate\">Margate</a> has suggested that the tales of Cannibal Bay may be explained as distorted reports of <a href=\"/index.php/Ice_dragon\" title=\"Ice dragon\">ice dragon</a> activity.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafbeyond_the_free_cities:_the_shivering_sea.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafbeyond_the_free_cities:_the_shivering_sea.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Cannibal_Bay&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafbeyond_the_free_cities:_the_shivering_sea.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafbeyond_the_free_cities:_the_shivering_sea.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafbeyond_the_free_cities:_the_shivering_sea.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Beyond the Free Cities: The Shivering Sea.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404015354\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.010 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.011 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 172/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 8568/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 840/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 446/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 1106/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    7.426      1 -total\n 76.82%    5.705      2 Template:Ref\n 46.00%    3.416      2 Template:Ref/core\n 21.41%    1.590      1 Template:References\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:19593-0!canonical and timestamp 20260404015354 and revision id 276256\n -->\n",
